      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agent): surface non_deliverable_terminal_turn with a specific retry message",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nSurfaces `non_deliverable_terminal_turn` with a specific retry message instead\nof the generic \"Agent couldn't generate a response\" fallback. The marker was\nalready classified but never surfaced to users.\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/types.ts` | Add `terminalError` to `EmbeddedRunAttemptResult` type |\n| `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/types.ts` | Add `terminalError` to `EmbeddedAgentRunMeta` type |\n| `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.ts` | Propagate `terminalError` from attemptTrajectoryTerminal |\n| `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run.ts` | Spread `terminalError` into incomplete_turn meta blocks |\n| `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-lifecycle-terminal.ts` | Add `terminalError` to deferred terminal metadata keys |\n| `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-failure-copy.ts` | Add `resolveExternalRunFailureTextForTerminalError` + constants |\n| `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.ts` | Wire `terminalError` into `buildExternalRunFailureReply` |\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Unit tests: terminal error propagation + fallback copy routing\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt-trajectory-status.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts\n\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  233 passed (233)\n   Duration  98.06s\n```\n\n### Retry-first copy\n\nWhen the model stops between tool calls without producing a reply:\n> ⚠️ The model stopped between tool calls without producing a reply. Please\n> try the same message again — this usually resolves on retry. If it\n> persists, use /new or a lighter model.\n\ninstead of the old generic fallback.\n\n_AI-assisted._",
